title.narrative: By 2021, the Government and other key stakeholders have the capacity to implement and monitor family support and community-basedchild care and protection services

description.narrative: The child protection system modeling was intensified in Attapeu and replicated in Xiengkhouang province. UNICEF technical and operational support contributed to developing the capacity of the social service workforce and allied workforce to implement and monitor family support and community-based childcare and protection services, including MHPSS, GBV/VAC, child justice, disability inclusion, etc. Despite COVID-19, UNICEF successfully expanded the child protection preventive and response services to 8, including new GBV/VAC reporting hotlines and free MHPSS mobile counselling services in five provinces. Innovative parenting education combined with saving for change enabled continued progress on behavior change and resilience building for parents. ; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/01/2022
